---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Cookie Policy | Orviq" description="Orviq Cookie Policy." locale="en-US">
    <main class="flex-grow pt-40 pb-24 px-6 md:px-16 max-w-[1440px] mx-auto">
        <header class="mb-16 max-w-3xl">
            <span class="text-xs text-primary uppercase tracking-[0.2em] mb-4 block font-semibold">Transparency</span>
            <h1 class="font-[Fraunces] text-4xl md:text-5xl lg:text-[64px] leading-[1.1] tracking-[-0.02em] font-semibold text-on-background mb-6">Cookie Policy</h1>
        </header>

        <article class="max-w-4xl legal-content">
            <p class="text-on-surface-variant">In compliance with Law 34/2002, of July 11, on Information Society Services and Electronic Commerce (LSSI) and current regulations on personal data protection, we inform users that the website <strong>https://orviq.net/</strong> (hereinafter, the "Website") uses cookies and similar technologies as data storage and recovery devices on users' terminal equipment. For more information about the website owner, please consult our <a href="/en/aviso-legal">Legal Notice</a>.</p>

            <h2>What are cookies?</h2>
            <p>Cookies are small text files that are stored on a user's device when accessing certain web pages. Their main purpose is to enable the technical operation of the website, facilitate navigation, remember preferences, or collect anonymous statistical information. These cookies do not damage the user's device and are essential for the proper functioning of the internet. When enabled in the browser, they help identify potential malfunctions and optimize website performance.</p>

            <h2>What types of cookies are used?</h2>
            <p>The ORVIQ website uses both its own and third-party cookies:</p>

            <h3>According to ownership</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>First-party cookies:</strong> these are sent to the user's device from a domain managed by ORVIQ, from which the requested service is provided.</li>
                <li><strong>Third-party cookies:</strong> these are sent to the user's device from a domain not managed by ORVIQ, but by another entity that processes the data obtained through these cookies.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>According to duration</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Session cookies:</strong> these are temporary and remain in the browser's cookie file until the user leaves the website. Their use is limited to facilitating navigation and providing basic functionalities. They do not collect personal data that can identify the user.</li>
                <li><strong>Persistent cookies:</strong> these are stored on the user's device for a specific period and allow remembering browsing information in subsequent visits, such as selected preferences or language.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>According to purpose</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Technical or necessary cookies:</strong> these are essential for the basic operation of the website, enabling functions such as navigation between sections, accessing secure areas, or user authentication. These cookies do not require user consent.</li>
                <li><strong>Preference or functionality cookies:</strong> these allow remembering choices made by the user (such as language, region, or login credentials), thus improving the browsing experience. The information stored by these cookies is generally anonymous.</li>
                <li><strong>Analysis or measurement cookies:</strong> these cookies allow quantifying the number of users and performing measurement and statistical analysis of how users use the website. Their purpose is to introduce improvements based on the analysis of aggregated navigation data. This data does not directly identify the user.</li>
                <li><strong>Marketing or behavioral advertising cookies:</strong> these allow analyzing the user's browsing habits to display advertising related to their profile. These cookies require the express consent of the user before being activated.</li>
            </ul>

            <h2>Details of the Cookies used by ORVIQ</h2>
            <p>Below is detailed information about the cookies that may be installed on the user's device through the Website:</p>

            <div class="overflow-x-auto mt-6 mb-8">
                <table class="w-full text-left border-collapse text-sm">
                    <thead>
                        <tr class="border-b border-surface-container-high">
                            <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-on-background">Controller</th>
                            <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-on-background">Category</th>
                            <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-on-background">Functionality</th>
                            <th class="py-3 pr-4 font-semibold text-on-background">Ownership</th>
                            <th class="py-3 font-semibold text-on-background">Duration</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody class="text-on-surface-variant">
                        <tr class="border-b border-surface-container-high/50">
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">ORVIQ</td>
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Technical</td>
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Management of cookie preferences and consent</td>
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">First-party</td>
                            <td class="py-3">1 year</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="border-b border-surface-container-high/50">
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Google (Fonts / Symbols)</td>
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Technical</td>
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Loading fonts and icons (fonts.googleapis.com, fonts.gstatic.com)</td>
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Third-party</td>
                            <td class="py-3">Session / 1 year</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="border-b border-surface-container-high/50">
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Cloudinary</td>
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Technical / Functional</td>
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Loading and playback of videos and media assets (res.cloudinary.com)</td>
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Third-party</td>
                            <td class="py-3">Session</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="border-b border-surface-container-high/50">
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Unsplash</td>
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Technical</td>
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Loading background images (images.unsplash.com)</td>
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Third-party</td>
                            <td class="py-3">Session</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr class="border-b border-surface-container-high/50">
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Formspree</td>
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Technical / Functional</td>
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Processing of contact forms and newsletters</td>
                            <td class="py-3 pr-4">Third-party</td>
                            <td class="py-3">Session</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>

            <h2>How to allow, reject or block cookies</h2>
            <p>When accessing the website for the first time, a cookie notice is displayed allowing the user to accept all cookies, reject them, or customize settings based on the type of cookie.</p>
            <p>Additionally, the user can configure their browser at any time to allow, block, or delete the cookies installed on their device. How to do this depends on the browser used. Below are direct links to cookie configuration instructions in the main browsers:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cookie settings for Google Chrome</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enable-and-disable-cookies-website-preferences" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cookie settings for Mozilla Firefox</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/delete-and-manage-cookies-168dab11-0753-043d-7c16-ede5947fc64d" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cookie settings for Internet Explorer</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://support.apple.com/en-gb/guide/safari/sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cookie settings for Safari</a></li>
                <li><a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cookie settings for Microsoft Edge</a></li>
            </ul>
            <p>Google also offers a <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">browser add-on</a> that allows you to disable Google Analytics analytical cookies in Chrome and other supported browsers.</p>
            <p>This website may use cookies on mobile devices. In such cases, the user can manage their preferences from the operating system settings: <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT201265" target="_blank" rel="noopener">iOS</a>, <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/windows" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Windows Phone</a>, <a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647?co=GENIE.Platform%3DAndroid" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Chrome Mobile</a>, <a href="https://www.opera.com/help/mobile/android#privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Opera Mobile</a>.</p>
            <p>The user is warned that disabling or deleting cookies may affect the proper functioning of the website.</p>

            <h2>Profiling</h2>
            <p>The Website may use third-party cookies for browsing profiling purposes aimed at displaying personalized advertising based on user interests. For more information on this processing, we recommend consulting the privacy policies of such third parties, accessible in the "Details of Cookies used by ORVIQ" section.</p>

            <h2>International data transfers</h2>
            <p>Some of the cookies used on this Website are managed by third parties whose services may involve international data transfers outside the European Economic Area (EEA). Detailed information on such transfers is available in the privacy policies of the corresponding providers.</p>

            <h2>Changes to the Cookie Policy</h2>
            <p>ORVIQ may modify this Cookie Policy to adapt it to new regulatory requirements, instructions from supervisory authorities, or technical improvements implemented on the Website. Any relevant changes will be communicated to the user by a notice on the Website itself or, where appropriate, through other suitable channels.</p>

            <h2>Additional Information</h2>
            <p>For more details on the processing of personal data, we invite you to consult our <a href="/en/privacidad">Privacy Policy</a> or contact us at <a href="mailto:orviq.contact@gmail.com">orviq.contact@gmail.com</a>.</p>
            <p>If the user needs assistance or has any further questions about the use of cookies on this website, you can write to us at <a href="mailto:orviq.contact@gmail.com">orviq.contact@gmail.com</a>.</p>

            <p class="text-sm text-on-surface-variant mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-surface-container-high">Last updated: April 19, 2026</p>
        </article>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.legal-content { line-height: 1.75; font-size: 1rem; }
.legal-content p { margin-bottom: 1.25rem; color: #b4b4c8; }
.legal-content h2 { font-family: 'Fraunces', serif; font-size: 1.6rem; font-weight: 600; color: #ffffff; margin-top: 2.5rem; margin-bottom: 1rem; padding-bottom: 0.5rem; border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.08); }
.legal-content h3 { font-size: 1.1rem; font-weight: 600; color: #e0e0f0; margin-top: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
.legal-content ul, .legal-content ol { margin-left: 1.5rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
.legal-content ul { list-style-type: disc; }
.legal-content ol { list-style-type: decimal; }
.legal-content li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; color: #b4b4c8; padding-left: 0.25rem; }
.legal-content strong { color: #e8e8f4; font-weight: 600; }
.legal-content a { color: #c4c0ff; text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
.legal-content a:hover { color: #ffffff; }
table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; font-size: 0.875rem; }
thead tr { border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.12); }
thead th { padding: 0.75rem 1rem 0.75rem 0; font-weight: 600; color: #e8e8f4; text-align: left; }
tbody tr { border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.05); }
tbody td { padding: 0.75rem 1rem 0.75rem 0; color: #b4b4c8; vertical-align: top; }
</style>
